My wife had a horrible experience with an extremely rude staff member at this location. Adam, who is either the owner or manager, told her to reach out to him. She emailed him 3 times with no response. Considering taking this issue to corporate.

This is an edit to my previous review- I had some issues with not getting comped for my returned bottles but the manager of the store, Adam, got back to me immediately and helped resolve the problem and was very nice/helpful.  As for the product, it is very good quality delicious milk and almost zero waste with the glass bottles. The main thing for our family was a need to cut back on plastic waste and Oberweis is the only company offering local milk in the old fashioned glass bottles. In addition, they have probably the best malts in the entire city. The chocolate malt especially is our favorite. My only advice is to make sure you directly talk to an employee and make sure you get your cash before setting you bottle-returns down by the door because otherwise there's a good chance whoever is working there won't go out of their way to give you your money back.

I want to add to this post: Adam below said to reach out so he could hear more and help-- I have now emailed him 3 times and he has yet to respond.  I went to Oberweis this weekend. I went into the store and a family of 6 was in front of me. The lines were a little confusing because on the right- it made it seem like the line was for the freezer section. There were also circles on the floor throughout. It was only the family of 6 and then myself in the store. The family ahead of me was taking a lot of room (which is totally fine), so I stood on a circle to the left and back of them while they ordered and got their food which took about 5-7 minutes. During this time, another larger family (4 people with kids), walked in and saw me. I guess they went to the left dots (near the freezer), I thought it was because the other family was in the middle and I was to the right- this made sense given the time of social distancing. Anyways... the family in front of me finishes, and I walk up to the register. The women at the register SCREAMS (not talks, not polite) at me that I was not in line and it is not my turn. The family of 4 who came in after me did not have an issue with this, as they saw I was there first and did no oppose. There are no dots that say- Wait here, next in line, etc. I chose a spot that was socially distant from kids running around, that was also as close as possible to the front of the line- as any normal, sane, person has. I should also mention I hadn't been to this store during covid times, so I was not aware of the process because to be honest, the dots on the floor and the order/organization isn't super obvious (which is fine if the staff are normal and accommodating). I turn to the family behind me to make sure it is okay I order, they say- yes, please order. I order my food. The rude cashier than yells at me 2 more times to tell me how I did not wait in the right place and it was not acceptable. Okay- GREAT, I get it. If there was a next time (which there will certainly not be) I know where to wait. I then pay, get my ice cream AND AGAIN, she made a rude comment in an unacceptable tone, telling me how I need to learn where to stand in the future. I could not believe that after the first conversation, which I was polite, and said, oh thank you for letting me know- i appreciate it and was trying to social distance, that she continued to bring this up and yell at me. I have never been treated this way, especially given the world we live in, it is unacceptable. I will not be returning to Oberweis and I suggest that management looks into the staff they hire.

What should have been a quick stop into Oberweis turned into a frustrating experience. We ordered two small milkshakes. Ten minutes go by, and we are still waiting. We have seen numerous people who came in after us receive their order. There is not one, not two, not three, but four workers besides the cashier making the ice cream. How hard is it for one person to throw ice cream into a blender?  We have now been waiting fifteen minutes, and we still haven’t received our shakes. I inform the cashier, who then after checking, returns and informs us that they lost our ticket, that they will start making our shakes now, and that it should be about five more minutes. So I’m expected to wait another five minutes, for a total of twenty, and pay full price? I don’t think so.  The cashier says we can either have our milkshakes made or we can receive a refund, but not both. What a joke. I ask for the refund. While refunding me, I inform her that another couple has been waiting even longer than we have and they might want to check on them. The cashier responds by telling me I’m being rude with her. What?! Meanwhile, the manager is right beside her, witnessing and hearing everything and does NOTHING!  That is not how you run a business or retain customers—I will never return.
